modules.description: This module sets metadata tags for MP3 files using the LAME encoder, including title, artist, album, year, comment, track number, and genre. It operates on the `Lame.encoder` type to embed textual information directly into audio files. Use this module to annotate encoded MP3s with descriptive tags for media organization and playback display.

This module provides bindings to the LAME library for encoding audio into MP3 format, allowing configuration of encoding parameters such as bitrate, sample rate, and channel layout. It operates on an `encoder` type that maintains encoding state and supports encoding both integer and floating-point audio buffers into MP3 frames. The `Id3tag` submodule extends the encoder with metadata tagging capabilities, enabling the embedding of title, artist, album, and other descriptive tags directly into the output files. Use this module to convert raw audio streams into compressed MP3 files with customizable quality settings and rich metadata annotations.
